==English==
===Noun===
'''arena'''
# An [[enclose]]d [[area]], often [[outdoor]], for the [[presentation]] of [[sport]]ing events or other [[spectacular]] events; earthen area, often oval, specifically for [[rodeo]]s (N. America) or circular area for [[bullfight]]s (esp. Hispanic America).
#: ''A large crowd filled the seats of the arena.''
# The [[building]] housing such an area.
#: ''The arena is grey with white beams.''
# ([[Ancient]] [[Rome]]) The [[sand]]-covered centre of an [[amphitheatre]] where [[contest]]s were held.
#: ''The gladiators entered the arena.''
# ([[Metaphorically]]) A place where important political or other events unfold.
#: ''The company was a player in the maritime insurance arena.''

====Translations====
*Roman arena ''f''

